contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox NRHP | name =Zumbro Parkway Bridge | nrhp_type = | image = zumbrofallsbridge.jpg | caption = Zumbro Parkway Bridge | nearest_city= [[Zumbro Falls, Minnesota]] | lat_degrees = 44 | lat_minutes = 16 | lat_seconds = 47 | lat_direction = N | long_degrees = 92 | long_minutes = 25 | long_seconds = 19 | long_direction = W | locmapin = Minnesota | area = | built =1937 | architect= Evans,J.M. | architecture= Other | added = November 6, 1989 | governing_body = Local | mpsub=Minnesota Masonry-Arch Highway Bridges MPS | refnum=89001824<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2007a}}</ref><ref name="nord">{{cite book|title=The National Register of Historic Places in Minnesota|last=Nord|first=Mary Ann|publisher=[[Minnesota Historical Society]]|year=2003|isbn=0-87351-448-3}}</ref> }} [[Image:Zumbrobridgegothic.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Zumbro Parkway Bridge, Gothic Cutouts]] The '''Zumbro Parkway Bridge''' is a [[steel arch bridge]] located in [[Zumbro Falls, Minnesota|Zumbro Falls]], [[Minnesota]]. The bridge was built in 1937 by the engineer [[J.M. Evans]] and is 59 feet long and 32.9 feet wide.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mnhs.org/places/nationalregister/bridges/nrwbzpb/nrwbzum.html |title=Minnesota's Historic Bridges - Zumbro Parkway Bridge | work=Minnesota Historical Society website |accessdate=2007-05-13}}</ref> It allows County 68 to cross a portion of the [[Zumbro River]]. The bridge is on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] (#89001824), and has been listed since 1989. ==References== {{Reflist}} {{Registered Historic Places}} [[Category:Arch bridges]] [[Category:Road bridges in Minnesota]] [[Category:Buildings and structures in Wabasha County, Minnesota]] [[Category:Zumbro River]] [[Category:Bridges completed in 1937]] [[Category:Bridges on the National Register of Historic Places in Minnesota]] [[Category:Transportation in Wabasha County, Minnesota]] {{Minnesota-NRHP-stub}} {{Minnesota-struct-stub}} {{US-bridge-struct-stub}}
